host_about:
I am new to Airbnb but my partner is not. – If you search " Hey, I’m Whitney! London, United Kingdom Member since September 2012 writer tour guide", you will see her Airbnb profile coming up towards the top with her profile picture with long hair in a dark dress. As you would see, she has been on Airbnb for around 3 years with around 100 positive reviews from former guests (some have mentioned me too) who have stayed in our spare rooms. I have moved into another apartment (a basement flat) at the same building as my partner, and now it is me welcoming you to my home!

I am someone of a cosmopolitan outlook, having lived in half a dozen countries and visited over 30 countries. I love the local London life here and interacting with local and international guests and friends.

What else about me? I drive classic cars (90s and 70s!) and I am into arthouse films, classical music and smooth nostalgic songs. My professional background is creative arts and science project and research management. I enjoy a variety of food from mild spice to super hot chili, and to burn off all those calories I work out everyday scoring long distance shots (half and three-quarter court) in basketball.

And you? Please do airbnb me as I am awaiting to welcome you here and get to know you!

Regards from London,
Kai (and Whitney)

name: Rental unit in Greater London · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
description:
A high-spec apartment on the banks of Regent's Canal, surrounded by the green spaces of Mile End Ecology Park, Victoria Park and the Olympic Park.

Shoreditch, Broadway Market, Columbia Flower Market and Lauriston Village all within walking distance.

Plus easy access to the City and to Canary Wharf (both a 20 min commute) - and with Bethnal Green station taking you directly to museums, Oxford St and Mayfair via the Central Line - you could not be better situated in the hub of East London.

The space
The apartment comprises a generous open plan kitchen-reception with a private balcony, a good sized bedroom and family bathroom.

Situated on the 7th floor of a secure block, the apartment has a concierge service, lift and secure cycle storage (underground car-parking can usually be arranged too).

South-facing, the private balcony benefits from the morning sun - and away from the road, the apartment is serenely quiet.
neighborhood_overview:
Hidden garden squares, secluded mews and some of the finest dining in the capital, the district of Bethnal Green & Bow has a rich and varied history and, today, is one of London’s most vibrant neighbourhoods. From our apartment, you can see across the canal to the steeples of the old Holy Trinity Church, which served the parish of Mile End Old Town in Victorian times. There, sits the Tredegar Square Conservation Area – an immaculately preserved enclave of Georgian squares, with two of our favourite pubs, the Lord Tredegar (at the north end) and the Morgan Arms (to the east).

Walking north along the canal, passing the distillery and bar of the East London Liquor Company, you’ll find the lakes and fountains of Victoria Park, with a Chinese pagoda and more than 86 sprawling hectares of greenery. Continue along the canal to reach the restaurants and brunch spots of Broadway Market. And from there, walk down to Columbia Road Flower Market, a bustling market where traders sell be
host_about:
My love of travel has taken me all around the world, staying in some thrilling places and meeting some amazing people. I am now rooted in London and love the diversity of people, places and culture that the city offers.  There's always something new to see, something different to do.

I have seen my fair share of hotels and holiday rentals, and strive to ensure that this apartment meets the requirements of even the most exacting of guests.

The space
Our space is NOT a business so don't expect an empty space void of belongings and personality. Intune with the original and founding Airbnb vibe, this is our home.

neighborhood_overview:
Kew is one of South West London's friendliest suburbs. Its vibe is safe, upmarket, green and we love it here!

Foodies or those seeking good coffee will be round the corner at Sift Bakes & Brews or eating at one of the independent cafes and restaurants in Kew Village including the 1 Michelin star, Glasshouse or our favourite, Antipodea less than 10 minutes walk away.

Culture vultures can enjoy the National Archives just next door to the apartment, home of the Domesday book or if you're more botanically minded, spend a day at the beautiful Kew Royal Botanical Gardens.

Weekend warriors can enjoy some of the best urban running or hiking in the country along the Thames Path National Trail. If spectating is more your thing, bbq and beers on Kew Green whilst watching the cricket is recommended. In nearby Brentford, home for the setting of Daniel Craig's film Layer Cake, Brentford FC's new championship stadium opens in 2020.

description:
One room in a 3-bedroom Kings Cross apartment located 12 minutes walk (or a 4 minute bus) from Kings Cross/St Pancras. The maisonette has recently been refurbished to be modern, quirky and spacious. The location is super for getting around London, the UK, Eurostar and all London airports. A short walk to Coal Drops Yard/Granary Square or Upper Street, both ace for independent shops and fantastic restaurants.

The space
The property has three bedrooms, but this listing is for one of them. The bedroom has a king-size four-poster bed, and towels will be provided.

Guests in this room are free to use the shared bathroom with spacious shower and heated towel rail.

Guest access
This booking includes access to the en-suit
neighborhood_overview:
We’re thrilled to offer you a comfortable stay in this area, we think it’s ace!

Here are a few of our recommended spots:

• Coal Drops Yard and Granary Square have a huge selection of lovely restaurants and cafes. Do nosey around yourselves, but we recommend Dishoom (modern Indian), Casa & Plaza Pastor (Mexican) and Caravan (eclectic)
• Upper Street has so many fantastic restaurants; you could eat at a fab new place every day for weeks! We recommend Le Mercury (French), Masala Zone (Indian) and The Breakfast Club (American and English)
• Supermarkets nearby include a large Waitrose (by Granary Square), a large Sainsbury's, another Waitrose and an M&S (by Angel station), Tesco Metro (by King's Cross) as well as an Iceland and two Co-ops (on Caledonian Road, with one in the petrol station)
• The nearest non-charging cash machine is around the corner to the right by the petrol station - there is also an Amazon locker here if you need something delivered
host_about:
Hello! I'm a freelance creative living in our recently renovated pad in Kings Cross with my husband. 

I’m a presenter and producer for both video and audio bits and bobs these days. I have previously worked in production for BBC Songs of Praise and pre-COVID was heard co-presenting a national breakfast radio show on Premier Christian Radio.

My husband John is more of the coding-kind and we are partial to dancing, bouldering and travelling ourselves. 

We're passionate about creating a hospitable, cosy family vibe for guests staying in our home. We’ve recently renovated it and are delighted to share the space we have created with folks and hope others get to be refreshed and enjoy some peace in our little oasis of London! We absolutely love the area and can give you our best recommendations of things to do that might suit your stay. 

Do drop us a message if you are interesting in staying in our home when we are away or with us in one of our two spare rooms! 

Hopefully see you soon! 

Rachel :)

neighborhood_overview:
Always be just 10 minutes from central London while having the best green spaces and canal routes on your doorstep. host_about:
Gabriella loves travelling and meeting people from all around the world.  
She often rents out the master bedroom in her flat to guests and shares the kitchen and dining room with them then; most of the reviews relate to that. Although friendly and sociable, she likes to have her own space; thus, she is  respectful of the need of others for privacy.  
Sometimes when she is away travelling she rents out the entire apartment, so those guests also get access to the large drawing room and will have the entire place to themselves.   
She is glad to advise about sightseeing in London and travel to other places in the UK, so please don’t hesitate to ask if you need help or guidance. 
As a guest she aims to be respectful, clean and tidy.
Her passions include reading, studying history, hiking in nature and yoga.

Your studio is completely private balcony, a bed, double sofa bed, a bathroom, TV, free wifi and fully functional kitchen that comes complete with oven, stove top, fridge kettle, toaster, pots & pans, glassware, crockery and cutlery.

neighborhood_overview:
You are right in the heart of one of the most colourful, vibrant and eclectic areas of London. Famous for the Brick Lane Sunday market and interesting shops, bars and restaurants are spread across the neighbourhood for you to explore everyday.
Columbia Road Flower market is only a short walk away held on Sundays. Liverpool Street is a 14 minute walk which connects you directly to the centre of London.
Broadway Market is close by and runs every Saturday, it is worthwhile checking it out!
On the way you will pass Spitafields market which is a great way to spend a few hours. It offers clothes, jewellery, vintage stalls, pop-up food vans and cafes.

We are situated in ZONE 1 which is central London but we are in the east side near Tower of London, St Pauls etc. We are not located near the West End (Covent Garden, Soho, Oxford st) but you will just have to catch a short train or bus ride there. neighborhood_overview: Chelsea is London's most desirable neighbourhood, so it's full of beautiful red-brick mansions and stucco-fronted townhouses. the flat is located just moments from Chelsea's main shopping street, Kings Road, which is full of designer outlets, boutique stores, trendy cafes and endless art galleries. The area is steeped in history: the Manor House of King Henry VIII is just a minute's walk from the flat, and the former house of Oscar Wilde is just a few minutes further. It's also credited as being the birthplace of punk fashion - Vivienne Westwood 's store on the Kings Road also located just moments from the flat. Battersea Park, Chelsea Embankment and Chelsea Physic Garden are also both close by, providing some tranquil and open space.

neighborhood_overview: Pimlico is an oasis in the centre of London. In between Victoria and Vauxhall, it is a quiet neighbourhood forgotten by time. With beautiful traditional architecture and an abundance of private garden squares, this furnished flat is in one of the most sought-after residential areas in the English capital. Walk around and you will find quaint shops, local high-quality restaurants and traditional pubs, all tucked away in hidden streets. In terms of transportation, you have Pimlico Underground on the Victoria Line within minutes away, offering easy connections into Central London. Westminster and Victoria Underground stations (District, Jubilee, Circle and Victoria lines) are also not far away and Victoria National Railway station has 30-minute connections into Gatwick airport, London’s second biggest Airport.

neighborhood_overview:
My street is a mews, set behind a row of shops. It's very hidden and quiet, with a really nice atmosphere.

It's just a 2 minute walk to Turnpike Lane tube station, on the Piccadilly Line, which has a really fast interchange with the Victoria Line at Finsbury Park (just walk across the platform). You can be in the centre of London in around 20 minutes.

My street is off Turnpike Lane, which is very international and has a range of interesting shops and takeaways. There is a large Turkish supermarket 2 minutes walk that can supply all your needs, but you are also 5 minutes walk from a larger Sainsbury's supermarket. You can also walk to Wood Green, a larger shopping area in 10 minutes. About 15 minutes walk away (or a quick bus ride) is Crouch End, which has some fancier shops and restaurants.

There are a lot of good takeaways in the area, notably a variety of authentic pizza places, burgers, Indian, Thai, and good sushi if you go to pick it up.

name: Rental unit in Greater London · ★4.71 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 4 baths
description:
An apartment you'll never forget!

A unique century-old gothic church tower, located in Hackney Wick, converted into a stunning home with a terrace enjoying beautiful 360-degree views of London. The church is Grade II* listed and was built for the Eton College Mission in 1894. The Tower has won the prestigious RIBA Architecture National Award. The penthouse conversion is incorporated within the 5 story church tower.

The space
The Tower is surrounded by a dynamic mix of historic Grade II-listed architecture and striking contemporary additions. The Anglican church tower defines the façade, stretching up over seven storeys and formed of red brick and stone, with truly impressive geometric arched fenestration. On one side is the contemporary diamond-patterned brickwork of Aumbrey Apartments, while the other side is formed of the remaining church buildings, which have also been converted to apartments, creating a peaceful community around the church green.
neighborhood_overview:
Hanging out in Hackney Wick is a happy way to spend an afternoon in vibrant East London. Once an enclave of industry with no real appeal, Hackney Wick now has a hipster vibe (but in a good way). Canalside culture, awesome apartment spaces, plenty of waterfront bars and restaurants combined with some of London’s best street-art should make this high on your London hit-list.

There are a lot of eateries to try here, including Number 90, a local favourite that is filled with homestyle food and tons of beer. Beer is pretty serious business in Hackney Wick and there are a few breweries and bars that offer a huge beer selection for aficionados. The Crate Brewery is our favourite of the lot.

Half of the fun getting to Hackney Wick is actually getting here – if you aren’t arriving by the London Overground, you’ll likely be arriving via one of the many canal towpaths in the area. Home to hundreds of houseboats and barges, there is very much a canalside community here with
host_about:
30 years old, ⁣
⁣
In addition to using Airbnb as a traveler, I also host our properties in London and in South Africa with my husband. 
⁣
Our adventures traveling and living abroad have been distilled into our apartments. All our homes are well designed, comfortable, clean, secure, and fully equipped with everything you will need to enjoy your holiday. I pride myself in being able to turn a "house into a home". I’m fun and easy-going and I’ve stayed in Airbnb’s all over the world and have met some great people through the platform. Welcome to Mili, a widebeam canal boat moored on a beautiful private pontoon. Mili is 60ft by 13ft, spacious with high ceilings. The private outdoor deck is shared with a neighbouring boat but you’re free to use the full space, feed the swans or just chill out and enjoy the riverside life :)

The boat is perfect for a couple's short holiday, you can enjoy a quiet and secluded space surrounded by water and wildlife...or you can go out and explore Hackney Wick creative neighbourhood!

The space
We have been living on Mili for two years and before that we lived on a cruising narrowboat called Hopkins. We’ve been slowly doing the boat up, painting and decorating and we hope you enjoy it as much as we do!

There’s a fully equipped kitchen, a living area with a wood burning stove, a bathroom with a walking shower and a master bedroom with a double bed.

Outside the boat we have a large floating wooden deck, a veg garden, outdoor tables an
neighborhood_overview:
Developing Hackney Wick is home to artist studios in former industrial spaces, quirky cafes, and creative eateries, with craft breweries and bars along the River Lee Navigation canal. The Here East business centre in the Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park houses hip restaurants and startups, while Olympic sports venues nearby include the London Stadium, now home to West Ham United soccer team, and Lee Valley Velopark.

Places we love:
Barge East - excellent food and drinks with a farmers market on Saturdays and Sundays.
Crate - famous brewery and delicious pizzas.
Doh - grocery and bakery, with makers market every weekends.
Howling Hoops - brewery with South American street food.
Silo - innovative zero-waste Brighton eatery.
Pavilion - great cafe in Victoria Park.

Activities:

neighborhood_overview:
Canary Wharf with its rich industrial past and present business buzz is home to many of London’s most prestigious ad agencies and financial giants.

This kinetic London Quarter is also peppered with a respectable ensemble of riverside brasseries, trendy diners like West India Quay’s Big Easy and iconic stops such as One Canada Square Restaurant and Bar. There are many more bars and restaurants around the docks and financial sector that will be perfect to take your clients and friends for a late night meal. For those that love a bit of history, there's the London Docklands Museum that provides huge insights into the area. With all this and more, you'll soon find that Canary Wharf isn't just a home for business but also one for pleasure.

The DLR has direct lines to Bank, Stratford and London City Airport. Your nearest DLR will be South Quay, although you can also catch the Jubilee Line at Canary Wharf station as an alternative, bit longer, route.

Apartments are prepared to a high standard for all our guests with clean linen and personalized check in. We are available to assist our guests 24*7 for any questions or recommendations.

Our team is dedicated to providing our guests with the best experience possible, so please do not hesitate to get in touch if you have any queries. 

We are happy to help and look forward to hosting you in London!

description:
This clean, quiet and very comfortable 1 bedroom flat is located 100m away from Chiswick Park tube station on District Line.

You will be 300m walk from Chiswick high road and have access to lots of amenities and restaurants nearby. The flat in on the first floor of a very secure devdevelopment with floor to ceiling windows facing Gunnersbury Triangle Nature Reserve.

The space
This is a 56 sqm 1 bedroom flat with a large private south-facing balcony to the Gunnersbury Triangle Nature Reserve. This flat is very quiet and filled with light.

You will have a king size bed (150*200) with a desk in the bedroom. In living room you will have a very comfortable double sofa bed (140*200) that can easily sleep two people and a fully equipped kitchen and a dining table.

Guest access
Guests will have access to the whole apartment.
neighborhood_overview: Chiswick is one of the liveliest and most kid friendly neighbourhoods of London with a flower, antique and cheese Market every first 3 Sundays of the month on the high road. You will have access to lots of local restaurants and cafes including a Michelin star restaurant on your door step. There are lots of green areas around you and river Thames will be 20 minutes walk away.
host_about:
My husband and I have been living in London for almost 8 years now. Prior to moving to UK we've lived in Switzerland, USA and Sweden for work and education. We truly love London and think it is one of kind. We usually use Airbnb for our travels and think its the best way to experience a city as a local. 

I've had another listing on Airbnb years ago before having my son. I'm very proud to say that I was a super host with a fully booked calendar during 11 months that I hosted in 2014 and 2015 with 4.87 stars of 116 reviews, 5 stars for cleanliness for all 116 reviews.

neighborhood_overview:
Located in West London, Hounslow is a thriving suburb that boasts excellent transport links to Central London. The opening of Heathrow Airport in 1946 brought considerable growth to the area. As Heathrow has continued to inexorably expand, so too has Hounslow.

The Treaty Centre, Hounslow’s indoor mall, contains over 40 stores, cafes and restaurants. It features an array of high-street fashion favourites to indulge in. Hounslow’s High Street contains a Global Food Market, giving visitors to the area a chance to experience sumptuous foods from around the world. A vast expanse of verdant plains, walkways and wildlife, Hounslow Heath was once used by Oliver Cromwell and King James II as a military camp, before being used as a hiding place for the notorious highwaymen. Now, the area is a peaceful retreat from the buzz of the city. Lampton Park and Inwood Park are less than fifteen minutes away, while Murray Park and Beaversfield Park are twenty minutes away.

neighborhood_overview: The flat is located in a beautiful town on the outskirts of London. Teddington is famous for its picturesque nature and  its close-knit community. Everything you might need is within walking distance including immaculate parks and friendly local shops. The Bushy Part gate is just 5 minutes away and the house is nearby the Thames Path National Trail beside London's rural Thames where the river rolls past palaces, and meadows, with the peaceful seclusion of willowy paths with nothing for company but wildflowers, birdsong and sky.
host_about:
Hi everyone. My name is Penelope. Welcome to my home! 

I have lived in London for 16 years now but I may assuredly now say that I am entirely aware of the culture and magnificent characteristics that this vibrant city entails. Let me ensure you that this place is worth your visit and you will be surprisingly delighted by the welcoming and the liveliness atmosphere of historical London. 

In my spare time, I love travelling, meeting new people, learning languages, cultures, and cuisines. Also, I love travelling to new places and meeting people. My most enjoyed places to visit is Germany, Austria and Italy. They are fantastic places full of history and culture. So if you ever need a suggestion for a great place to eat, let me know and I would love to help you out. 

I joined Airbnb because I love to travel in my spare time but now I have decided to host as well. Being a host is of high importance to me because it allows me to be helpful to the visitors, whereas I can imagine, it may be difficult to orientate yourself in the first few days of arriving at a new setting. I find it very exciting to host people from all across the world! I would count myself as a "hands-on" host because I believe it is essential to be there for your guest. The main rule I live by is "treat people how you would like to be treated", and I will be sure to treat you with the utmost respect. With that in mind, I may confidently state that I will be reliable, friendly and an organised host to make your stay as smooth as possible. 

Consequently, I decided that Airbnb is a great opportunity to be useful for travellers that come to tour and explore the incredible London. In my profile, you will be able to find a selection of accommodations to choose from based on your liking. I hope you enjoy your stay whilst I will try to provide you with immediate assistance to ensure that you have an outstanding trip! For a better experience of my guests, my listings are handled by a dedicated property management company who will do everything to guarantee that your stay will be impeccable. I hope you enjoy your stay in London!

host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 

Please be aware once a booking is confirmed you will be required to complete a Rental Agreement and also  ID verification via our partners Superhog. This is mandatory for all our stays and in accordance to short lets requirements with Veeve.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 

Please be aware once a booking is confirmed you will be required to complete a Rental Agreement and also  ID verification via our partners Superhog. This is mandatory for all our stays and in accordance to short lets requirements with Veeve.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

name: Loft in Greater London · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
description:
This newly refurbished artist's studio loft is situated in the heart of the creative and vibrant Notting Hill Area. Just around the corner of countless cafes, bakeries, Delis and wonderful vintage shops. It is my favourite part of Portobello Road, not so touristy and with plenty of cool cafés just minutes away. Your ideal chance to feel like a local! The location is great, 2 minutes away from the Bus stop and 8 min from Ladbroke Grove Station (the Station in the middle of Portobello Road).

The space
The flat has been newly renovated. The decoration is minimal and with Japanese aesthetics. I'm an artist and architect myself, so there's a lot of care put into this space. You'll find everything that you can need, and the kitchen is fully equipped so that you can also cook if you choose to do so. It is a very cosy flat.
neighborhood_overview: Notting Hill is famous for its colourful houses, the Portobello Market on the weekends, the Street Food and the amazing cafés and bars. My favourite bakery "Layla Bakery" for the best croissant and coffee breakfast is just around the corner. Lowry & Bake, Bluebelles of Portobello and the Golborne Deli are also just minutes away. You won't want to leave this neighbourhood! There are many supermarkets closeby, basically everything that you need. I recommend walking down Portobello Road and explore all of the cute little corners of this neighbourhood. Also, the canal that leads to Little Venice is minutes away from the flat, another lovely walk!

neighborhood_overview:
About the area – Mayfair
Mayfair is one of the most exclusive areas in the heart of London. It borders onto Hyde Park to the west, Oxford Street to the north, Piccadilly and Green Park to the south and Regent Street to the east.

Mayfair is perfectly located for shopping and entertainment. Famous establishments within close proximity of Mayfair House include Savile Row, Burlington Arcade, the Ritz Hotel and the West End theatre district. New and Old Bond Street, known for fine jewellery, antiques and clothing is also nearby. This is also home to Sotheby’s, one of Mayfair’s oldest and most respected auction houses.

A short his­tory: the area of May­fair was first devel­oped around 1686 and became the site for the annual May Fayre (a 15 day cel­e­bra­tion from May Day and thought to have started in the days of Edward I to mark St James Day), a com­bi­na­tion of mar­ket, enter­tain­ment and mer­ri­ment, and very pop­u­lar annual event. host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 

Please be aware once a booking is confirmed you will be required to complete a Rental Agreement and also  ID verification via our partners Superhog. This is mandatory for all our stays and in accordance to short lets requirements with Veeve.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 

Please be aware once a booking is confirmed you will be required to complete a Rental Agreement and also  ID verification via our partners Superhog. This is mandatory for all our stays and in accordance to short lets requirements with Veeve.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

Queen's Park is known for family-friendly living, the area is centred around a park of 30 acres (12 ha), which opened in 1887 and was named to honour Queen Victoria. Architecturally, Queen's Park is an important historic area, with a unified urban layout with a high level of building preservation. The park is a good example of a Victorian urban green space, and the surrounding streets largely comprise original two- and three-storey Victorian buildings.

Kilburn is an area of north west London, England, which spans the boundary of two London Boroughs: Camden to the east and Brent to the west. There is also an area in the London Borough of Westminster, known as West Kilburn and sometimes treated as a distinct locality. The area is identified in the London Plan as one of 35 major centres in Greater London.
